<section class="marketing-shell">
  <div class="hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">hifumi · 一二三 · hi-fu-mi</span>
    <h1 class="h-display">Build Rails apps from a chat prompt.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Describe the app — hifumi plans <code class="mono">revisions</code>, drives Claude through
      implement → verify → commit, and hands you a clean Rails repo.
      Bring your own OpenRouter key. No vendor lock-in.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-actions">
      <%= link_to "Sign up", new_user_registration_path, class: "btn btn--accent" %>
      <%= link_to "Log in", new_user_session_path, class: "btn btn--outline" %>
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="section-rule">

  <div class="pipeline">
    <div class="pipeline-step">
      <div class="pipeline-step__numeral kanji">一</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__label">hi · 01 · describe</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__title">You describe the app</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__body">
        Type a sentence — “a flower shop with checkout,” or paste a 200-line spec.
        Hifumi asks for clarifications, then plans the work as a sequence of small,
        named revisions.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pipeline-step">
      <div class="pipeline-step__numeral kanji">二</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__label">fu · 02 · build</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__title">Hifumi builds, revision by revision</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__body">
        A <code class="mono">Roast</code> workflow drives Claude through
        implement → verify → commit on a real Rails repo. Each revision is one
        atomic git commit you own.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pipeline-step">
      <div class="pipeline-step__numeral kanji">三</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__label">mi · 03 · run</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__title">You run the result</div>
      <div class="pipeline-step__body">
        Preview the app in a hardened Docker container at
        <code class="mono">&lt;id&gt;.preview.hifumi.dev</code>.
        Clone the repo, take it elsewhere — your dependencies, your git history.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="section-rule">

  <div style="padding: 64px 0; text-align: center;">
    <p class="lede" style="margin: 0 auto; max-width: 640px;">
      Rails Way first — convention over configuration.
      Output is a clean Rails repo, no SaaS theatre.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
